I may have accounted for one or two of those smartwatch sales. I was looking for something that could help me feel a little safer by notifying my loved ones when I had a seizure (using 3rd party stuff that works with smartwatches), as they tend to set in very quickly. I have had quite a few seizures without anyone knowing about it and it always terrifies me. I did however end up sending them back and giving up on that idea, partly because they had terrible battery life.

That's kind of depressing to think about, actually. I'd really had hope for that, as it is it's been some time since then and I still don't feel safe.
